{{Quote|He is the ''one'' we have waited for&hellip; Bring him to the ''Temple of Fire!''|translated=1|Zythmnr, after seeing the unconscious Exar Kun|<ref name="DLotS4" />}}
The '''Temple of Fire''', also known as '''Tmmn Zyrth''' in the [[Massassi (language)|Massassi language]], was a [[Massassi/Legends|Massassi]] temple on the [[Moon/Legends|moon]] [[Yavin 4/Legends|Yavin 4]] used for [[Blood/Legends|blood]] sacrifices.<ref name="DLotS4" /> It was built in [[5000 BBY/Legends|5000 BBY]]<ref name="NEC" /> under the leadership of the [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Dark Lord of the Sith]] [[Naga Sadow/Legends|Naga Sadow]].<ref name="FotSE5" /> 

[[File:Tfotse12.jpg|200px|thumb|left|Massassi built the temple in 5000 BBY.]]
Designed as a cone-shaped structure,<ref name="DLotS4" /> the Temple concealed Sadow's ship, the [[Derriphan-class battleship|''Derriphan''-class battleship]] [[Corsair (Derriphan-class)|''Corsair'']], beneath the floor.<ref name="DLotS5">[[Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith 5|''Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith'' 5]]</ref> Sadow was aware of an [[Dark Lord prophecy|ancient prophecy]] about the return of the [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Dark Lords of the Sith]] and placed a mighty [[Sithspawn/Legends|Sithspawn]] beast known as a [[Sith wyrm]] within the temple as a guardian against the future Dark Lord of the Sith.<ref name="DLotS4" />

When [[Exar Kun/Legends|Exar Kun]] arrived on the moon, he was captured by the Massassi and led to that temple to be executed. However, using the dark power of the [[Sith talisman/Legends|Sith amulets]], he defeated the Sith wyrm that Sadow had created and was worshiped as a god by the Massassi.<ref name="DLotS4" />

In [[3996 BBY]],<ref name="NEC" /> the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]] created a [[Wall of light]] that destroyed the Temple of Fire.<ref name="destruction">[[The Official Star Wars Fact File 37|''The Official Star Wars Fact File'' 37]] says that the Temple of Fire was destroyed in [[Battle of Yavin 4 (Great Sith War)|Exar Kun's final battle with the Jedi]], during which [[Tales of the Jedi – The Sith War 6|''Tales of the Jedi – The Sith War'' 6]] shows all Jedi coming together to create a wall of light.</ref>

